26/01/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- On Friday (24 January), High Representative Paddy Ashdown imposed a new set of laws designed to help fight organised crime.
The package includes a new criminal code and a witness protection programme.Ashdown, the top international official in BiH, also authorised the newly deployed EU police mission in BiH to dismiss local staff in case of misconduct and lack of discipline.
In other news, a court in Mostar charged a Muslim man with killing three ethnic Croats.
Muamer Topalovic has confessed to committing the murders out of religious fanaticism.
(AFP - 25/01/03;
AP, AFP - 24/01/03)
